00:53:43,517 --> 00:53:44,449
Excuse me.

771
00:53:44,585 --> 00:53:46,018
I'd like you all to know
this young lady

772
00:53:46,153 --> 00:53:48,018
and I are getting married!

773
00:53:55,429 --> 00:53:56,896
''She agreed with all her heart...

774
00:53:57,030 --> 00:54:00,966
...but couldn't understand why
at the very moment she said yes...

775
00:54:01,101 --> 00:54:03,262
...Noah's face came to her mind.''

776
00:54:14,514 --> 00:54:15,981
Hey, look at you!

777
00:54:16,883 --> 00:54:19,317
Good to see you. Let me see you.

778
00:54:19,786 --> 00:54:21,344
You bleeding anywhere? No?

779
00:54:21,488 --> 00:54:22,682
-Everything good?
-Yeah.

780
00:54:22,823 --> 00:54:24,188
Oh, I love you.

781
00:54:26,193 --> 00:54:28,218
-There's something I got to show you.
-All right.

782
00:54:28,362 --> 00:54:29,056
Come on.

783
00:54:33,734 --> 00:54:36,635
what's going on? What is this?

784
00:54:37,170 --> 00:54:38,102
Here.

785
00:54:38,772 --> 00:54:39,898
I sold the house.

786
00:54:41,375 --> 00:54:42,399
You sold the house?

787
00:54:42,542 --> 00:54:44,942
Yep. Got to be out by the end
of the month.

788
00:54:45,078 --> 00:54:48,309
Between that and your GI Bill you ought
to be able to get it now.

789
00:54:48,949 --> 00:54:49,711
Get what?

790
00:54:49,850 --> 00:54:52,045
Your dream house.
The Windsor Plantation.

791
00:54:52,185 --> 00:54:54,210
-Dad--
-I don't want to hear about it.

792
00:54:54,354 --> 00:54:56,686
I already talked to the bank.
They'll give you the loan.

793
00:54:58,158 --> 00:55:01,457
-Well, I can't let you sell your house.
-lt's done.

794
00:55:02,029 --> 00:55:04,088
lt's a good thing, you should do it.

795
00:55:11,371 --> 00:55:14,272
Wait a second. You sell the house,
where you going to live?

796
00:55:14,408 --> 00:55:18,208
With you, dummy. Where do you think?
Somebody's got to help you fix it up.

797
00:55:27,454 --> 00:55:31,220
''Noah took a look at the house,
but only saw one thing:

798
00:55:31,992 --> 00:55:33,016
Allie.

799
00:55:34,394 --> 00:55:37,852
He decided right there
to fulfill his lifelong dream.

800
00:55:38,465 --> 00:55:41,491
He would rebuild the old house
from the ground up.

801
00:55:44,371 --> 00:55:48,899
And when Noah went to Charleston
to get the building plans approved...

802
00:55:49,042 --> 00:55:50,509
...fate stepped in...

803
00:55:50,977 --> 00:55:53,070
...and dealt him a sweet card.''

804
00:56:00,454 --> 00:56:01,546
Stop the bus!

805
00:56:02,255 --> 00:56:02,721
Stop the bus!

806
00:56:02,856 --> 00:56:05,256
I can't stop till I get to the depot.

807
00:56:05,392 --> 00:56:07,155
No. Please stop the bus now.

808
00:56:07,294 --> 00:56:12,027
You understand English? No one gets off
till we get to ghe depot. Sit down!

809
00:56:12,165 --> 00:56:13,655
God--

810
00:56:20,440 --> 00:56:21,236
Move!

811
00:56:21,975 --> 00:56:22,873
What are you doing?!

812
00:56:28,048 --> 00:56:29,106
He's right over there.

813
00:56:47,267 --> 00:56:49,201
Baby. Hello.

814
00:57:14,094 --> 00:57:15,823
''After seeing Allie that day...

815
00:57:15,962 --> 00:57:18,157
...something inside Noah snapped.

816
00:57:19,065 --> 00:57:19,759
He got the notion...

817
00:57:19,900 --> 00:57:24,530
...that if he restored the old house
where they had come that night...

818
00:57:24,671 --> 00:57:27,231
...Allie would find a way
to come back to him.

819
00:57:28,108 --> 00:57:30,508
Some called it a labor of love.

820
00:57:30,844 --> 00:57:32,869
Others called it something else.

821
00:57:33,013 --> 00:57:36,540
But in fact, Noah had gone a little mad.

822
00:57:37,651 --> 00:57:39,084
-When--''
-Excuse me?

823
00:57:39,719 --> 00:57:41,414
lt's time to eat.

824
00:57:41,755 --> 00:57:44,223
Lunch is in the sun room today.

825
00:57:46,193 --> 00:57:48,923
The melon is good. I had a bite.

826
00:57:49,996 --> 00:57:51,827
Do they ever see each other again?

827
00:57:52,566 --> 00:57:53,897
Noah and Allie?

828
00:57:54,734 --> 00:57:59,637
You don't want me to spoil the end
before I get to the good part, do you?

829
00:58:00,874 --> 00:58:02,933
Where did I leave off?

830
00:58:03,343 --> 00:58:04,310
''I shall not want...''

831
00:58:04,444 --> 00:58:06,844
''When Noah's father died in November...

832
00:58:06,980 --> 00:58:08,880
...the house was all he had.

833
00:58:29,436 --> 00:58:32,166
ln time, Noah finished the house.''

834
00:58:32,305 --> 00:58:33,602
Smile. Here we go.

835
00:58:36,510 --> 00:58:38,774
''He took a good look at what
he had accomplished...

836
00:58:38,912 --> 00:58:41,813
...got rip-roaring drunk for 10 days...

837
00:58:41,948 --> 00:58:44,508
...thought seriously
about setting it on fire...

838
00:58:44,918 --> 00:58:47,011
...and finally put the house up
for sale.''

839
00:58:47,153 --> 00:58:49,553
I'm prepared to offer you this much.

840
00:58:50,824 --> 00:58:52,849
''He had a number of interested buyers.

841
00:58:52,993 --> 00:58:55,962
But he always found a reason
not to sell it to them.''

842
00:58:56,096 --> 00:58:57,154
No.

843
00:58:57,297 --> 00:58:59,424
''Either their bids were too low...

844
00:58:59,566 --> 00:59:04,060
...or if they met his asking price,
he felt it was worth a lot more.''

845
00:59:04,337 --> 00:59:05,861
lt's a lot of money...

846
00:59:06,006 --> 00:59:07,530
...but I'll take it.

847
00:59:10,277 --> 00:59:11,938
Fifty thousand dollars.

848
00:59:12,078 --> 00:59:13,602
That's more than my asking price.

849
00:59:13,747 --> 00:59:17,046
That's right. lt's a great deal more.

850
00:59:21,121 --> 00:59:24,557
''He told the man that offered him $5000
over his price...

851
00:59:24,691 --> 00:59:27,489
...that no one in his right mind
would do that...

852
00:59:27,627 --> 00:59:30,721
...and he wouldn't have a lunatic
living in his house.

853
00:59:32,799 --> 00:59:37,099
He worked out his frustration with life
on the creek every morning.

854
00:59:38,405 --> 00:59:41,897
And in the evenings,
to temper ths ting of loneliness...

855
00:59:42,042 --> 00:59:43,669
...there was Martha Shaw.

856
00:59:44,711 --> 00:59:48,579
Martha was a war widow who lived
in Quail Ridge, a town away.''

857
00:59:53,386 --> 00:59:55,547
So you want to go out to eat tomorrow?

858
00:59:55,956 --> 00:59:57,548
I got to work.

859
00:59:57,691 --> 00:59:59,852
We can go down to the river if you want.

860
00:59:59,993 --> 01:00:01,585
Next week sometime.

861
01:00:01,928 --> 01:00:03,691
Maybe we could take a drive somewhere.

862
01:00:03,830 --> 01:00:04,990
No.

863
01:00:05,632 --> 01:00:07,964
Well, I'm just asking you.

864
01:00:19,312 --> 01:00:20,609
What do you want, Noah?

865
01:00:24,250 --> 01:00:26,013
What do you mean what do I want?

866
01:00:28,588 --> 01:00:29,953
From me.

867
01:00:35,629 --> 01:00:38,530
sometimes when you talk to me
you don't even see me.

868
01:00:43,436 --> 01:00:47,497
Look, a woman knows when a man looks
into her eyes and sees someone else.

869
01:00:54,681 --> 01:00:57,377
Now, you know I want to give you
all the things that you want.

870
01:00:59,252 --> 01:01:00,412
Right?

871
01:01:04,791 --> 01:01:06,156
But I can't...

872
01:01:08,194 --> 01:01:09,923
...because they are gone.

873
01:01:12,599 --> 01:01:13,725
They're broken.

874
01:01:17,237 --> 01:01:18,226
All right?

875
01:01:42,829 --> 01:01:43,853
Is the veil too much?

876
01:01:43,997 --> 01:01:46,124
Are you kidding? You look perfect.

877
01:01:46,266 --> 01:01:48,234
You're the most beautiful bride.

878
01:01:50,837 --> 01:01:52,896
-You look gorgeous, honey.
-Thank you.

879
01:01:53,039 --> 01:01:57,135
Wait until Lon sees you in this dress.
He's going to go crazy!

880
01:01:57,277 --> 01:01:59,245
He won't be able
to take his eyes off you.

881
01:01:59,379 --> 01:02:00,778
Or his hands.

882
01:02:00,914 --> 01:02:02,711
Oh, you are so bad.

883
01:02:02,849 --> 01:02:04,339
Have you seen this morning's paper?

884
01:02:04,484 --> 01:02:08,818
The Daily Journal says you are going to
be the social highlight of the season.

885
01:02:08,955 --> 01:02:09,785
The season?

886
01:02:09,923 --> 01:02:12,551
This'll be a celebration the lokes of
which this town had never seen!

887
01:02:13,460 --> 01:02:16,793
She doesn't plan,
she plots, doesn't she?

888
01:02:18,064 --> 01:02:19,759
Mana, look, the governor's coming.

889
01:02:19,899 --> 01:02:21,457
He better. Letme see.

890
01:02:25,038 --> 01:02:26,164
Oh, boy.

891
01:02:53,700 --> 01:02:56,134
-Savannah, where are we at?
-We're at 82 now.

892
01:03:04,477 --> 01:03:06,411
-Memphis, where are we at?
-We're at 89.

893
01:03:06,546 --> 01:03:07,808
-Great. Up from 85.
-Sir?

894
01:03:07,947 --> 01:03:09,676
-Yes?
-You have a visitor.

895
01:03:11,518 --> 01:03:13,782
Well, hello.
Baby, I didn't know you were coming.

896
01:03:13,920 --> 01:03:17,014
I'm so sorry. I should've called.

897
01:03:17,157 --> 01:03:19,352
What are you talking about?
You don't have to call.

898
01:03:20,627 --> 01:03:22,925
-Guys, could you give us a minute?
-Yes, sir.

899
01:03:23,530 --> 01:03:25,361
-Miss Allie.
-Ma'am.

900
01:03:31,771 --> 01:03:32,795
So, what's up?

901
01:03:36,009 --> 01:03:37,567
I don't paint anymore.

902
01:03:38,745 --> 01:03:42,909
I used to paint all the time
and I really loved it.

903
01:03:43,550 --> 01:03:44,482
I didn't know that.

904
01:03:44,617 --> 01:03:45,709
Yeah.

905
01:03:48,254 --> 01:03:49,414
So paint.

906
01:03:50,089 --> 01:03:51,021
I will.

907
01:03:51,624 --> 01:03:53,785
Yeah, I'm going to start.

908
01:03:55,528 --> 01:03:56,460
Great.

909
01:04:02,602 --> 01:04:03,534
Is everything okay?

910
01:04:06,906 --> 01:04:08,533
I need to get away.

911
01:04:09,809 --> 01:04:10,798
Okay.

912
01:04:11,144 --> 01:04:15,604
I need to take care of a few things.
I need to clear my head.

913
01:04:15,748 --> 01:04:17,375
Okay, should I be worried?

914
01:04:18,318 --> 01:04:19,683
No, I don't think so.

915
01:04:19,819 --> 01:04:21,684
Well, that's reassuring.

916
01:04:23,289 --> 01:04:27,225
-Listen, are you all right?
-Yeah.

917
01:04:27,360 --> 01:04:31,888
Okay. Then go. Take your time.
Do whatever you need to do.

918
01:04:32,031 --> 01:04:33,328
lt's okay to be nervous.

919
01:04:33,466 --> 01:04:35,457
lt's normal to get cold feet
before your wedding.

920
01:04:35,602 --> 01:04:38,765
No. No second thoughts, Lon.

921
01:04:42,742 --> 01:04:43,834
I love you.

922
01:04:44,577 --> 01:04:47,944
And I'm going to be back from Seabrook
in a couple of days, Okay?

923
01:04:48,715 --> 01:04:50,148
Seabrook.

924
01:04:50,283 --> 01:04:51,944
Yeah. Seabrook.

925
01:05:38,765 --> 01:05:39,754
Hello.

926
01:05:44,404 --> 01:05:46,599
I waw your picture in the paper.

927
01:05:47,340 --> 01:05:49,035
The one with you and the house.

928
01:05:49,175 --> 01:05:51,700
and I just wanted to come
and see if you were okay.

929
01:05:52,312 --> 01:05:55,110
I mean, I wasn't in the neighborhood
or anything. I just...

930
01:06:03,189 --> 01:06:04,486
So are you okay?

931
01:06:09,195 --> 01:06:10,093
Okay, good.

932
01:06:15,401 --> 01:06:18,131
I'm a stupid woman.
I shouldn't have come.

933
01:06:39,459 --> 01:06:41,051
You want to come in?

934
01:06:41,194 --> 01:06:42,218
Okay.

935
01:06:45,999 --> 01:06:47,261
this is a good story.

936
01:06:47,867 --> 01:06:48,993
I'm glad you like it.

937
01:06:51,871 --> 01:06:53,099
I think I've heard it before.

938
01:06:55,141 --> 01:06:56,233
Yes.

939
01:06:57,477 --> 01:06:59,172
Perhaps more than once?

940
01:07:00,079 --> 01:07:01,603
Doctor needs to see you.

941
01:07:01,748 --> 01:07:02,942
Me? Now?

942
01:07:03,082 --> 01:07:04,106
No. Him.

943
01:07:04,250 --> 01:07:06,411
But he hasn't finished reading
the story.

944
01:07:06,552 --> 01:07:08,747
I'll read more
when I'm through with the doctor.

945
01:07:08,888 --> 01:07:10,913
lt shouldn't take too long.

946
01:07:11,057 --> 01:07:13,787
-All right.
-Don't you go away. I'll be right back.

947
01:07:16,029 --> 01:07:18,896
While you waiting,
maybe you'd like to play the piano.

948
01:07:19,032 --> 01:07:20,522
You do like that.

949
01:07:20,666 --> 01:07:21,564
I do?

950
01:07:23,002 --> 01:07:24,128
I don't know any tunes.

951
01:07:24,270 --> 01:07:25,897
You can read music.

952
01:07:26,305 --> 01:07:27,829
No kidding.

953
01:07:33,479 --> 01:07:34,446
Who are you?

954
01:07:34,580 --> 01:07:37,549
I'm Dr. Barrwell,
one of the new attending physicians.

955
01:07:38,017 --> 01:07:40,952
We haven't met,
so I thought I'd examine you myself.

956
01:07:43,356 --> 01:07:45,221
Okay, so I see here that

957
01:07:45,358 --> 01:07:48,452
you've had two heart attacks over
the last 18 months.

958
01:07:48,594 --> 01:07:51,062
Yeah, minor ones.
I think one was angina.

959
01:07:51,197 --> 01:07:52,129
Okay, any complications?

960
01:07:52,265 --> 01:07:53,892
Nope. Feel fine.

961
01:07:54,033 --> 01:07:55,500
Okay. Deep breath for me.

962
01:07:57,236 --> 01:07:58,863
Okay. One more time.

963
01:08:00,406 --> 01:08:01,873
And deep breath.

964
01:08:03,209 --> 01:08:04,642
And one more.

965
01:08:06,746 --> 01:08:09,579
Terrific. Terrific.
You still taking your medication?

966
01:08:09,715 --> 01:08:11,182
Every day, twice a day.

967
01:08:11,484 --> 01:08:14,385
Good, good, good, good, good.
Okay, you can put your shirt on.

968
01:08:20,059 --> 01:08:22,619
So I understand that
you read to Miss Hamilton.

969
01:08:22,762 --> 01:08:24,855
Yep. To help her remember.

970
01:08:26,499 --> 01:08:27,989
You don't think it'll help.

971
01:08:28,134 --> 01:08:29,795
No, I don't.

972
01:08:29,936 --> 01:08:35,374
She remembers, doc.
I read to her and she remembers.

973
01:08:35,508 --> 01:08:38,375
Not always, but she remembers.

974
01:08:38,511 --> 01:08:42,675
Senile dementia is irreversible.
lt's degenerative.

975
01:08:42,815 --> 01:08:45,613
After a certain point,
its victims don't come back.

976
01:08:45,751 --> 01:08:47,241
That's what they keep telling me.

977
01:08:47,520 --> 01:08:49,283
I just don't want you
to get your hopes up.

978
01:08:49,422 --> 01:08:52,823
Well, thanks, doc.
But you know what they say:

979
01:08:52,959 --> 01:08:56,156
Science goes only so far
and then comes God.

980
01:08:56,629 --> 01:08:58,494
Then comes God.

981
01:09:00,633 --> 01:09:03,033
Damn, they forgot
to turn the page for her.

982
01:09:03,169 --> 01:09:04,659
You through with me?

983
01:09:23,489 --> 01:09:25,320
I guess they flipped that page.

984
01:09:25,892 --> 01:09:27,154
No.

985
01:09:27,793 --> 01:09:30,353
That, she's playing by memory.

986
01:09:31,597 --> 01:09:33,656
His name is Lon Hammond, Jr.

987
01:09:33,799 --> 01:09:34,731
Hammond?

988
01:09:34,867 --> 01:09:36,858
As in Hammond Cotton?

989
01:09:37,003 --> 01:09:38,971
As in Hammond Cotton.

990
01:09:39,238 --> 01:09:41,502
Well, your parents must love him.

991
01:09:41,774 --> 01:09:43,639
He's a really good man, Noah.

992
01:09:43,776 --> 01:09:45,175
You'd really like him.

993
01:09:46,512 --> 01:09:47,604
You love him?

994
01:09:48,681 --> 01:09:49,909
Yeah.

995
01:09:50,249 --> 01:09:52,911
I do. I love him very much.

996
01:10:00,726 --> 01:10:01,920
Well, that's that.

997
01:10:02,195 --> 01:10:05,392
You marry Lon, and we can be friends.

998
01:10:07,400 --> 01:10:08,526
Right?

999
01:10:09,435 --> 01:10:10,333
Right.

1000
01:10:15,775 --> 01:10:16,799
Are you hungry?

1001
01:10:18,110 --> 01:10:19,338
You want to stay for dinner?

1002
01:10:31,691 --> 01:10:33,886
I have to warn you, I'm a cheap drunk.

1003
01:10:34,327 --> 01:10:36,818
Couple more of these and you'll be
carrying me right out of here.

1004
01:10:37,163 --> 01:10:38,027
Well, go slow, then.

1005
01:10:38,164 --> 01:10:39,961
I don't want to have to take advantage
of you.

1006
01:10:40,099 --> 01:10:43,398
You wouldn't dare. I 'm a married woman.

1007
01:10:43,669 --> 01:10:44,567
Not yet.

1008
01:10:51,344 --> 01:10:52,208
What?

1009
01:10:55,514 --> 01:10:57,277
Why are you looking at me like that?

1010
01:11:00,353 --> 01:11:01,547
Just memories.

1011
01:11:06,859 --> 01:11:07,826
This room.

1012
01:11:11,897 --> 01:11:12,864
This--

1013
01:11:13,399 --> 01:11:14,832
Is this where--?

1014
01:11:15,768 --> 01:11:17,292
This is the room?

1015
01:11:33,052 --> 01:11:33,984
I'm full.

1016
01:11:34,420 --> 01:11:35,284
Me too.

1017
01:11:39,392 --> 01:11:41,292
''O, how your fingers drowse me.

1018
01:11:41,594 --> 01:11:43,755
Your breath falls around me like dew.

1019
01:11:43,896 --> 01:11:46,956
Your pulse lulls the tympans of my ears.

1020
01:11:47,099 --> 01:11:49,567
I feel immerged from head to foot.

1021
01:11:49,702 --> 01:11:51,567
Delicious, enough.''

1022
01:11:53,406 --> 01:11:55,374
lt was real, wasn't it?

1023
01:11:57,143 --> 01:11:57,871
You and me?

1024
01:11:59,845 --> 01:12:03,713
Such a long time ago.
We were just a couple of kids.

1025
01:12:07,453 --> 01:12:09,887
But we really loved each other,
didn't we?

1026
01:12:18,664 --> 01:12:19,528
I should go.

1027
01:12:23,569 --> 01:12:24,593
Goodbye.

1028
01:12:27,139 --> 01:12:28,868
You think you could come back
tomorrow morning?

1029
01:12:29,608 --> 01:12:31,633
There's some place I'd like to show you.

1030
01:12:35,214 --> 01:12:36,112
Please?

1031
01:12:37,450 --> 01:12:38,178
Okay.

1032
01:12:39,018 --> 01:12:39,848
Okay.

1033
01:12:52,965 --> 01:12:55,900
''She had come back into his life
like a sudden flame...

1034
01:12:56,502 --> 01:12:58,766
...blazing and streaming into his heart.

1035
01:13:00,473 --> 01:13:01,872
Noah stayed up all night...

1036
01:13:02,007 --> 01:13:05,135
...contemplating the certain agony
he knew would be his...

1037
01:13:05,277 --> 01:13:06,801
...if he were to lose her twice.''

1038
01:13:07,780 --> 01:13:11,648
Oh, I do wish I could figure out
the end of this story.

1039
01:13:11,784 --> 01:13:13,046
The children are here.

1040
01:13:14,487 --> 01:13:15,920
Children?

1041
01:13:16,322 --> 01:13:18,085
Not yours, his.

1042
01:13:19,325 --> 01:13:20,292
Do you mind?

1043
01:13:20,426 --> 01:13:21,984
Oh, I'd love to meet them.

1044
01:13:23,662 --> 01:13:25,994
-Come over here.
-Hi Daddy.

1045
01:13:26,132 --> 01:13:27,190
-How are you?
-Good.

1046
01:13:27,333 --> 01:13:29,528
-How you doing, Maggie?
-Hi, Daddy.

1047
01:13:30,236 --> 01:13:32,204
Hi. I'm Allie.

1048
01:13:32,705 --> 01:13:34,502
-Hi, I'm Mary Allen.
-Mary Allen.

1049
01:13:34,640 --> 01:13:36,437
-Nice to see you.
-Nice to see you.

1050
01:13:36,809 --> 01:13:37,867
-Hi.
-Hi.

1051
01:13:38,010 --> 01:13:40,205
-Maggie.
-Maggie, how are you?

1052
01:13:40,846 --> 01:13:42,245
Hello there, honey.

1053
01:13:42,381 --> 01:13:43,678
Hi. Davanee.

1054
01:13:43,816 --> 01:13:46,444
-what a pretty name.
-Thank you.

1055
01:13:47,219 --> 01:13:49,949
Oh, my. Thank you.

1056
01:13:51,924 --> 01:13:54,449
-And who's this?
-Edmond.

1057
01:13:54,593 --> 01:13:55,685
Hi, Edmond.

1058
01:14:07,373 --> 01:14:12,834
You know, I think I'll run on up
and take my afternoon nap. All right?

1059
01:14:12,978 --> 01:14:15,378
-Come on, honey. Let's go.
-There you go.

1060
01:14:15,514 --> 01:14:17,948
-All right. Good.
-Thank you.

1061
01:14:18,083 --> 01:14:19,448
I'll read some more later.

1062
01:14:20,052 --> 01:14:21,349
All right. Thank you.

1063
01:14:22,555 --> 01:14:24,546
I'm so happy to meet you all.

1064
01:14:26,859 --> 01:14:28,520
-Goodbye.
-Nice to meet you.

1065
01:14:28,661 --> 01:14:30,561
-Goodbye.
-Bye.

1066
01:14:32,298 --> 01:14:33,890
She seems good today.

1067
01:14:34,033 --> 01:14:35,694
She is good.

1068
01:14:36,435 --> 01:14:38,335
I don't know,
there's something about today.

1069
01:14:39,738 --> 01:14:41,706
Maybe it's a day for a miracle.

1070
01:14:43,509 --> 01:14:44,601
Daddy...

1071
01:14:45,644 --> 01:14:46,770
...come home.

1072
01:14:47,379 --> 01:14:48,971
Mama doesn't know us.

1073
01:14:49,114 --> 01:14:52,641
She doesn't recognize you.
She'll never understand.

1074
01:14:52,785 --> 01:14:56,482
We miss you.
This is crazy, you living here.

1075
01:14:56,622 --> 01:14:59,318
Yeah. You know, we'll all help with Mon.

1076
01:14:59,458 --> 01:15:01,619
We can take shifts visiting.

1077
01:15:02,294 --> 01:15:05,161
Look, guys...

1078
01:15:05,297 --> 01:15:06,924
...that's my sweetheart in there.

1079
01:15:07,900 --> 01:15:08,958
I'm not leaving her.

1080
01:15:10,603 --> 01:15:12,230
This is my home now.

1081
01:15:13,405 --> 01:15:15,396
Your mother is my home.

1082
01:15:21,780 --> 01:15:22,906
-Hello?
-Hey there.

1083
01:15:23,048 --> 01:15:24,276
Hi.

1084
01:15:25,017 --> 01:15:26,211
Who is this?

1085
01:15:26,352 --> 01:15:27,785
lt's Lon. Who were you expecting?

1086
01:15:27,920 --> 01:15:33,517
Nobody. I'm just surprised.
How did you find me?

1087
01:15:33,659 --> 01:15:35,149
Well, there's only one hotel
in Seabrook.

1088
01:15:35,294 --> 01:15:37,888
And when you didn't call, I got worried.

1089
01:15:38,030 --> 01:15:41,022
Where have you been? Are you all right?

1090
01:15:41,367 --> 01:15:44,302
I feel like an idiot because I called
your hotel about a hundred times.

1091
01:15:46,405 --> 01:15:48,168
I'm fine.

1092
01:15:49,008 --> 01:15:51,033
-Anything you want to tell me?
-No.

1093
01:15:51,443 --> 01:15:52,467
No?

1094
01:15:52,611 --> 01:15:53,703
No.

1095
01:15:57,850 --> 01:15:58,817
Okay.

1096
01:16:01,654 --> 01:16:03,121
Lon, I love you.

1097
01:16:03,656 --> 01:16:05,021
Call you tomorrow?

1098
01:16:06,025 --> 01:16:06,992
Okay.

1099
01:16:38,657 --> 01:16:39,521
Noah?!

1100
01:16:40,793 --> 01:16:41,521
Noah?!

1101
01:16:58,544 --> 01:16:59,340
Hey there.

1102
01:17:05,818 --> 01:17:07,718
Well, we better get going.
The rain's coming in.

1103
01:17:33,612 --> 01:17:34,601
You like it?

1104
01:17:41,687 --> 01:17:42,676
lt's like a dream.

1105
01:17:44,523 --> 01:17:46,150
Do you want to feed them?

1106
01:17:46,291 --> 01:17:47,417
Yeah.

1107
01:18:05,110 --> 01:18:06,372
What are they all doing here?

1108
01:18:08,347 --> 01:18:09,541
I don't know.

1109
01:18:10,382 --> 01:18:13,317
They're supposed
to migrate to Wadmalaw Sound.

1110
01:18:13,619 --> 01:18:15,143
They won't stay here?

1111
01:18:15,287 --> 01:18:16,219
No.

1112
01:18:17,890 --> 01:18:19,721
They'll go back where they came from.

1113
01:18:32,504 --> 01:18:33,528
You're different.

1114
01:18:35,040 --> 01:18:36,166
What do you mean?

1115
01:18:37,643 --> 01:18:39,167
Just the way you look.

1116
01:18:39,678 --> 01:18:40,906
Everything.

1117
01:18:41,180 --> 01:18:43,512
You look different too,
but in a good way.

1118
01:18:49,621 --> 01:18:51,111
You know,
you're kind of the same, though.

1119
01:18:53,258 --> 01:18:54,384
Yeah?

1120
01:18:55,594 --> 01:18:56,424
Yeah.

1121
01:18:59,331 --> 01:19:00,696
And you really did it.

1122
01:19:01,834 --> 01:19:02,698
What?

1123
01:19:03,001 --> 01:19:03,797
Everything.

1124
01:19:04,870 --> 01:19:05,837
The house.

1125
01:19:07,940 --> 01:19:09,703
lt's beautiful what you did.

1126
01:19:13,178 --> 01:19:14,975
Well, I promised you I would.

1127
01:19:25,190 --> 01:19:26,122
Great.

1128
01:19:27,893 --> 01:19:29,019
We got to go.

1129
01:20:00,392 --> 01:20:01,324
Noah!

1130
01:20:54,313 --> 01:20:55,803
Why didn't you write me?

1131
01:20:57,249 --> 01:20:58,238
Why?

1132
01:20:59,484 --> 01:21:01,179
lt wasn't over for me.

1133
01:21:01,653 --> 01:21:04,144
I waited for you for seven years.

1134
01:21:04,723 --> 01:21:06,623
And now it's too late.

1135
01:21:07,125 --> 01:21:10,253
I wrote you 365 letters.

1136
01:21:11,830 --> 01:21:13,491
I wrote to you every day for a year.

1137
01:21:14,867 --> 01:21:16,664
-You wrote me?
-Yes.

1138
01:21:18,303 --> 01:21:19,565
lt wasn't over.

1139
01:21:21,273 --> 01:21:23,002
lt still isn't over.

1140
01:23:33,138 --> 01:23:34,628
You got to be kidding me.

1141
01:23:36,742 --> 01:23:38,607
All this time,
that's what I've been missing?

1142
01:23:43,815 --> 01:23:45,077
Let's do it again.

1143
01:23:59,197 --> 01:24:00,357
Noah.

1144
01:24:21,987 --> 01:24:23,011
Noah.

1145
01:24:31,897 --> 01:24:32,955
Wake up.

1146
01:24:35,000 --> 01:24:35,932
Wake up.

1147
01:24:44,342 --> 01:24:47,209
-Hi.
-You're trying to kill me, woman.

1148
01:24:53,452 --> 01:24:54,612
I need rest.

1149
01:24:55,754 --> 01:24:59,588
I need food so I can regain my strength.

1150
01:25:00,592 --> 01:25:01,524
Okay.

1151
01:25:02,527 --> 01:25:03,323
What do you want?

1152
01:25:09,034 --> 01:25:10,524
Some pancakes.

1153
01:25:11,336 --> 01:25:12,098
Okay.

1154
01:25:12,971 --> 01:25:14,996
And some bacon...

1155
01:25:16,041 --> 01:25:16,837
Okay.

1156
01:25:17,275 --> 01:25:18,537
And some chicken.

1157
01:26:04,322 --> 01:26:05,949
She's the one, isn't she?

1158
01:26:12,697 --> 01:26:13,994
Can I meet her?

1159
01:26:17,202 --> 01:26:20,763
-I'd really like to meet her.
-l don't know if that's a good idea.

1160
01:26:23,542 --> 01:26:24,736
So this is Martha?

1161
01:26:26,077 --> 01:26:27,101
Hi.

1162
01:26:28,146 --> 01:26:29,306
I'm Allie.

1163
01:26:29,781 --> 01:26:31,305
I've heard a lot about you.

1164
01:26:32,284 --> 01:26:34,047
I've heard a lot about you too.

1165
01:26:34,953 --> 01:26:36,147
You want to come in?

1166
01:26:38,790 --> 01:26:39,722
Are you sure?

1167
01:26:39,858 --> 01:26:43,726
Yeah. Yeah. Noah was just saying
how hungry he was.

1168
01:26:43,862 --> 01:26:45,796
You know you could put on a pot of tea.

1169
01:26:47,699 --> 01:26:48,723
Come on in.

1170
01:26:52,370 --> 01:26:53,462
Come on in.

1171
01:27:03,615 --> 01:27:06,106
-lt was nice meeting you, Martha.
-Nice meeting you too.

1172
01:27:06,418 --> 01:27:07,942
-Bye.
-Take care.

1173
01:27:28,006 --> 01:27:29,439
She's sensational.

1174
01:27:30,408 --> 01:27:31,602
She really is.

1175
01:27:32,711 --> 01:27:34,804
I'm really glad that I came, Noah.

1176
01:27:40,118 --> 01:27:42,086
I'd forgotten what it's like.

1177
01:27:46,291 --> 01:27:48,851
For the first time since
I lost Richard...

1178
01:27:49,394 --> 01:27:52,557
...I feel like I've got something
to look forward to.

1179
01:30:10,902 --> 01:30:12,199
Lon is on his way here.

1180
01:30:15,840 --> 01:30:17,740
I'm afraid your father spilled
the beans about Noah.

1181
01:30:17,876 --> 01:30:20,845
When Lon didn't hear from you again,
he decided to come.

1182
01:30:20,979 --> 01:30:22,241
Well, that's great.

1183
01:30:23,047 --> 01:30:23,945
That's just terrific.

1184
01:30:24,082 --> 01:30:27,142
You, me, Noah and Lon.
One big happy family.

1185
01:30:33,158 --> 01:30:35,126
Tell me about the letters, Mother.

1186
01:30:35,927 --> 01:30:36,791
Is it true?

1187
01:30:37,228 --> 01:30:38,320
Yes.

1188
01:30:39,798 --> 01:30:44,132
You watched me cry myself to sleep
for months and months...

1189
01:30:44,269 --> 01:30:46,294
...and you never said anything.

1190
01:30:47,038 --> 01:30:48,835
-How could you do that?
-I'm sorry.

1191
01:30:48,973 --> 01:30:50,304
-You're sorry?
-Yes, I am. I am sorry.

1192
01:30:50,442 --> 01:30:52,569
Because of you,
my entire life was ruined.

1193
01:30:52,710 --> 01:30:54,837
Yes, I stole your letters. lt was wrong.

1194
01:30:54,979 --> 01:30:58,471
But stop being dramatic and at least
take some of the resposibility.

1195
01:31:00,218 --> 01:31:03,312
You came down here.
You knew what you were doing.

1196
01:31:03,455 --> 01:31:04,422
You knew this would happen.

1197
01:31:04,556 --> 01:31:05,921
so now I'm a tramp?

1198
01:31:06,724 --> 01:31:09,522
You are unbelievable. Unbelievable.

1199
01:31:14,432 --> 01:31:15,865
Come on. Get some clothes on.

1200
01:31:17,669 --> 01:31:18,897
Let's take a drive.

1201
01:31:19,237 --> 01:31:19,760
''Let's take a drive.''

1202
01:31:19,904 --> 01:31:22,065
Why would I want to go anywhere
with you?

1203
01:31:22,207 --> 01:31:25,176
Because I might know you
a little better than you think.

1204
01:31:26,578 --> 01:31:29,479
I don't want you waking up one morning
thinking if you'd known everything...

1205
01:31:29,614 --> 01:31:31,445
...you might've done
something different.

1206
01:31:45,997 --> 01:31:47,123
What are we doing here, Mama?

1207
01:31:49,634 --> 01:31:52,068
Do you see that man there?

1208
01:32:00,044 --> 01:32:03,070
Doesn't look like it now,
but 25 years ago...

1209
01:32:04,516 --> 01:32:07,349
Oh, my goodness.
He was really something.

1210
01:32:07,685 --> 01:32:10,313
We were out of our minds in love,
let me tell you.

1211
01:32:15,260 --> 01:32:16,249
Wow.

1212
01:32:17,295 --> 01:32:19,126
Well, naturally your grandfather
was furious,

1213
01:32:19,264 --> 01:32:21,789
so we decided to run away.

1214
01:32:25,003 --> 01:32:28,495
We didn't even maked the next town
before the police picked us up.

1215
01:32:31,776 --> 01:32:32,868
But that was then.

1216
01:32:35,446 --> 01:32:38,142
You know, sometimes
when I'm in the area...

1217
01:32:38,516 --> 01:32:41,246
...I just stop here and watch him...

1218
01:32:44,022 --> 01:32:47,253
...trying to picture how different
my life might have been.

1219
01:33:01,639 --> 01:33:04,005
I want you to know that
I love your father.

1220
01:33:05,043 --> 01:33:05,600
Mama...

1221
01:33:05,743 --> 01:33:08,211
No, goddamn it, this is important
and you need to hear it.

1222
01:33:08,613 --> 01:33:11,946
I do. He is a wonderful man.

1223
01:33:12,083 --> 01:33:14,415
He is good to me,
and I don't deserve him.

1224
01:33:15,386 --> 01:33:17,718
I love him, Allie, I do. I love him.

1225
01:33:17,855 --> 01:33:19,379
I know you love him, Mama.

1226
01:33:21,459 --> 01:33:22,551
I know.

1227
01:33:27,599 --> 01:33:28,861
Oh, my God.

1228
01:33:31,669 --> 01:33:36,197
This is just very embarrassing.
I am a stupid woman.

1229
01:33:37,842 --> 01:33:39,639
Look at me, a big old bawl bag.

1230
01:33:43,414 --> 01:33:44,506
lt's crazy...

1231
01:33:52,924 --> 01:33:56,724
...but I don't even know
who that person is.

1232
01:34:05,403 --> 01:34:06,301
Oh, boy.

1233
01:34:45,810 --> 01:34:46,708
Allie!

1234
01:35:04,295 --> 01:35:05,523
Here.

1235
01:35:10,201 --> 01:35:12,692
I hope you make the right choice.

1236
01:35:40,031 --> 01:35:41,123
lnteresting morning.

1237
01:35:42,333 --> 01:35:43,231
Yeah.

1238
01:35:45,837 --> 01:35:47,236
Lon's here in town.

1239
01:35:50,475 --> 01:35:51,601
He's here?

1240
01:35:54,512 --> 01:35:57,879
Yeah we saw his car on the way,
at the hotel.

1241
01:36:08,526 --> 01:36:10,016
I see you got my letters.

1242
01:36:14,031 --> 01:36:14,895
Finally.

1243
01:36:22,874 --> 01:36:23,966
What are you going to do, Al?

1244
01:36:28,780 --> 01:36:29,678
I don't know.

1245
01:36:37,588 --> 01:36:38,782
We're back to that?

1246
01:36:41,492 --> 01:36:42,720
Are we back there?

1247
01:36:44,996 --> 01:36:47,794
What about the past couple of days?
They happened, you know.

1248
01:36:47,932 --> 01:36:50,162
I know they happened
and they were wonderful.

1249
01:36:50,301 --> 01:36:52,462
But they were also very irresponsible.

1250
01:36:53,237 --> 01:36:56,695
I have a fiance waiting for me
who'll be crushed when he finds out--

1251
01:36:56,841 --> 01:37:00,436
So you make love to me
and then you go back to your husband?

1252
01:37:01,145 --> 01:37:02,635
Is that your plan?

1253
01:37:02,780 --> 01:37:05,374
-Was that a test that I didn't pass?!
-No! I made a promise to a man.

1254
01:37:05,516 --> 01:37:06,915
I gave him my word.

1255
01:37:07,051 --> 01:37:08,916
Your word is shot to hell now,
don't your think?

1256
01:37:09,053 --> 01:37:10,850
I'll find out when I talk to him.

1257
01:37:10,988 --> 01:37:15,857
This is not about keeping your promise.
And it's not about following your heart.

1258
01:37:16,594 --> 01:37:17,720
lt's about sceurity.

1259
01:37:17,862 --> 01:37:19,727
-What is that supposed to mean?
-Money!

1260
01:37:19,864 --> 01:37:21,832
-What are you ta--?
-He has a lot of money!

1261
01:37:21,966 --> 01:37:23,831
-I hate you, you smug bastard.
-I hate you.

1262
01:37:23,968 --> 01:37:25,162
If your leave here, I hate you.

1263
01:37:25,303 --> 01:37:28,170
Haven't you paid attention
to anything that's happened?

1264
01:37:28,306 --> 01:37:30,536
I guess not. I must have misread
all of those signals.

1265
01:37:30,675 --> 01:37:31,972
Yeah, I guess you did.

1266
01:37:34,846 --> 01:37:37,610
You're bored! You're bored
and you know it.

1267
01:37:37,748 --> 01:37:39,978
You wouldn't be here
if there wasn't something missing.

1268
01:37:40,618 --> 01:37:42,518
Arrogant son of a bitch.

1269
01:37:44,121 --> 01:37:45,713
Would you just stay with me?

1270
01:37:45,990 --> 01:37:48,686
Stay with you? What for?
Look at us. We're already fighting.

1271
01:37:48,826 --> 01:37:52,284
Well, that's what we do. We fight.

1272
01:37:52,530 --> 01:37:54,293
You tell me
when I'm an arrogant son of a bitch.

1273
01:37:54,432 --> 01:37:56,696
I tell you
when you're a pain in the ass,

1274
01:37:56,834 --> 01:37:59,462
which you are 99% of the time.

1275
01:38:00,137 --> 01:38:04,096
I'm not afraid to hurt your feelings.
They have a two-second rebound rate...

1276
01:38:04,242 --> 01:38:07,006
...and you're back doing
the next pain-in-the-ass thing.

1277
01:38:07,678 --> 01:38:08,235
So what?

1278
01:38:08,379 --> 01:38:11,314
So it's not going to be easy.
lt's going to be really hard.

1279
01:38:11,749 --> 01:38:15,480
We'll have to work at this every day,
but I want to because I want you.

1280
01:38:15,620 --> 01:38:17,747
I want all of you forever.

1281
01:38:17,889 --> 01:38:19,857
You and me every day.

1282
01:38:19,991 --> 01:38:21,515
Will you do something for me?

1283
01:38:22,593 --> 01:38:23,491
Please?

1284
01:38:23,628 --> 01:38:25,892
Will you just picture
your life for me...

1285
01:38:27,098 --> 01:38:29,089
...30 years from now, 40 years from now.

1286
01:38:29,233 --> 01:38:30,427
What's it look like?

1287
01:38:30,801 --> 01:38:32,632
If it's with that guy, go.

1288
01:38:32,770 --> 01:38:36,001
Go! I lost you once,
I think I could do it again...

1289
01:38:36,140 --> 01:38:38,608
...if I thought it's what
you really wanted.

1290
01:38:38,876 --> 01:38:41,936
-But don't you take the easy way out.
-What easy way?

1291
01:38:42,079 --> 01:38:45,139
There is no easy way.
No matter whta I do, somebody gets hurt.

1292
01:38:45,283 --> 01:38:47,683
Would you stop thinking
about what everyone wants?

1293
01:38:48,386 --> 01:38:51,913
Stop thinking about what I want.
What he wants. What your parents want.

1294
01:38:52,456 --> 01:38:53,616
What do you want?

1295
01:38:54,892 --> 01:38:56,883
-What do you want?
-lt's not that simple.

1296
01:38:57,028 --> 01:38:59,121
What do you want?

1297
01:39:01,599 --> 01:39:03,464
Goddamn it, what do you want?

1298
01:39:06,537 --> 01:39:07,504
I have to go.

1299
01:40:17,408 --> 01:40:19,603
My dearest Allie:

1300
01:40:19,744 --> 01:40:20,733
I couldn't sleep last night

1301
01:40:20,878 --> 01:40:23,039
because I know that
it's over between us.

1302
01:40:24,882 --> 01:40:28,181
I'm not bitter anymore because I know
that what we had was real.

1303
01:40:30,021 --> 01:40:34,583
If in some distant place in the future
we see each other in our new lives...

1304
01:40:34,725 --> 01:40:36,955
...I'll smile at
your with joy and remember...

1305
01:40:37,094 --> 01:40:39,562
...how we spent a summer beneath
the trees...

1306
01:40:40,431 --> 01:40:43,093
...learning from each other
and growing in love.

1307
01:41:01,018 --> 01:41:04,215
The best love is the kind that awakens
the soul...

1308
01:41:04,355 --> 01:41:05,982
...and makes us reach for more.

1309
01:41:06,857 --> 01:41:11,123
That plants a fire in our hearts
and brings peace to our minds.

1310
01:41:11,929 --> 01:41:13,453
And that's what you've given me.

1311
01:41:14,999 --> 01:41:17,467
That's what I had hoped
to give to you forever.

1312
01:41:18,536 --> 01:41:21,664
''I love you. I'll be seeing you. Noah.''

1313
01:41:23,140 --> 01:41:24,266
lt's beautiful.

1314
01:41:25,609 --> 01:41:26,974
lt's a beautiful story.

1315
01:41:27,111 --> 01:41:28,305
Yes, it is.

1316
01:41:28,846 --> 01:41:31,406
I don't know why,
but it makes me feel sad.

1317
01:41:34,418 --> 01:41:37,512
I know you feel lost right now,
but don't worry.

1318
01:41:38,255 --> 01:41:41,156
''Nothing is ever lost or can be lost.

1319
01:41:41,525 --> 01:41:44,824
The body, sluggish, aged, cold...

1320
01:41:44,962 --> 01:41:48,728
...the embers left from earlier fires...

1321
01:41:48,866 --> 01:41:50,629
...shall duly flame again.''

1322
01:41:52,970 --> 01:41:54,267
Did you write that?

1323
01:41:54,405 --> 01:41:55,565
No.

1324
01:41:55,706 --> 01:41:57,333
That was Walt Whitman.

1325
01:41:59,910 --> 01:42:01,468
I think I knew him.

1326
01:42:01,946 --> 01:42:03,311
I think you did.

1327
01:42:05,182 --> 01:42:08,276
Shall we go in?
I'm feeling a little chilly.

1328
01:42:11,255 --> 01:42:12,153
Thank you.

1329
01:42:22,600 --> 01:42:23,999
Who did all of this?

1330
01:42:24,135 --> 01:42:28,196
I did, with a little help
from my friends on the nursing staff.

1331
01:42:43,287 --> 01:42:45,585
I've never seen anything so beautiful.

1332
01:42:46,891 --> 01:42:48,290
Neither have l.

1333
01:42:51,929 --> 01:42:53,089
Shall we?

1334
01:43:01,238 --> 01:43:03,138
-Some grape juice?
-I'd love it.

1335
01:43:06,010 --> 01:43:08,410
Wow, so many pills. How sick are you?

1336
01:43:09,079 --> 01:43:12,776
Well, ''sickness'' has
become a relative term for me.

1337
01:43:12,917 --> 01:43:17,377
I think of it now as more
a general wearing-out process.

1338
01:43:19,690 --> 01:43:20,679
To you.

1339
01:43:29,433 --> 01:43:30,593
So, what happened?

1340
01:43:31,835 --> 01:43:33,063
ln the story?

1341
01:43:33,537 --> 01:43:35,061
Which one did she choose?

1342
01:43:42,746 --> 01:43:44,805
The way I see it, I got three choices.

1343
01:43:45,783 --> 01:43:47,751
One, I can shoot him.

1344
01:43:48,652 --> 01:43:51,120
Two, I can kick the crap out of him.

1345
01:43:51,622 --> 01:43:52,714
Or three...

1346
01:43:53,757 --> 01:43:55,247
...I leave you.

1347
01:44:00,931 --> 01:44:02,922
But all that's no good.

1348
01:44:05,269 --> 01:44:06,463
You see, because...

1349
01:44:08,539 --> 01:44:11,007
...none of those options give me you.

1350
01:44:13,877 --> 01:44:15,401
And in spite of everything...

1351
01:44:17,548 --> 01:44:18,674
...I love you.

1352
01:44:21,051 --> 01:44:22,177
I love you too.

1353
01:44:23,954 --> 01:44:26,286
I meant what I said
when I gave you that ring.

1354
01:44:26,490 --> 01:44:27,650
I did too.

1355
01:44:27,791 --> 01:44:28,758
I did too.

1356
01:44:28,892 --> 01:44:32,487
lt's just that when I'm with Noah
I feel like one person...

1357
01:44:32,630 --> 01:44:35,360
...and when I'm with you
I feel like someone totally different.

1358
01:44:38,302 --> 01:44:39,030
Look...

1359
01:44:39,570 --> 01:44:42,539
...it's normal not to forget
your first love.

1360
01:44:49,847 --> 01:44:50,939
I love you, Allie.

1361
01:44:52,383 --> 01:44:54,408
But I wnat you for myself.

1362
01:44:55,419 --> 01:44:59,378
I don't want to have to convince
my fiancee she should be with me.

1363
01:45:01,592 --> 01:45:02,991
You don't have to.

1364
01:45:04,161 --> 01:45:06,493
I already know I should be with you.

1365
01:45:08,732 --> 01:45:11,326
''And they lived happily ever after.''

1366
01:45:11,635 --> 01:45:12,693
Who?

1367
01:45:13,370 --> 01:45:14,359
Who did?

1368
01:45:22,446 --> 01:45:23,913
Oh, yes.

1369
01:45:25,949 --> 01:45:27,473
Of course.

1370
01:46:09,393 --> 01:46:10,792
I remember now.

1371
01:46:13,664 --> 01:46:14,688
lt was us.

1372
01:46:15,666 --> 01:46:19,534
-lt was us. lt was us.
-Oh, my darling. Oh, my sweetheart.

1373
01:46:20,704 --> 01:46:23,138
I love you so much.

1374
01:46:25,008 --> 01:46:27,272
Oh, my baby.

1375
01:46:29,046 --> 01:46:31,776
Noah. Noah.

1376
01:46:31,915 --> 01:46:33,405
I love you, angel.

1377
01:46:36,153 --> 01:46:37,450
What happened to me?

1378
01:46:37,821 --> 01:46:41,120
Nothing.
You just went away for a little while.

1379
01:46:45,028 --> 01:46:46,518
How much time to we have?

1380
01:46:46,897 --> 01:46:47,886
I'm not sure.

1381
01:46:49,299 --> 01:46:51,767
Last time it was no more
than five minutes.

1382
01:46:56,940 --> 01:46:58,567
Hey...

1383
01:46:58,709 --> 01:47:00,939
...I brought along an old friend.

1384
01:47:41,718 --> 01:47:44,448
-How are the children?
-Oh, they're fine.

1385
01:47:44,988 --> 01:47:49,288
They were here today.
Little Noah. Davanee too.

1386
01:47:49,960 --> 01:47:51,587
They're getting so big.

1387
01:47:53,564 --> 01:47:54,588
Oh, boy.

1388
01:47:56,200 --> 01:47:57,997
How fast the time goes.

1389
01:48:00,170 --> 01:48:01,637
Just flies right on by.

1390
01:48:01,772 --> 01:48:03,706
Oh, yes, it does.

1391
01:48:09,079 --> 01:48:11,013
Will you tell them I love them?

1392
01:48:12,216 --> 01:48:13,342
Of course I will.

1393
01:48:15,052 --> 01:48:16,383
And that I'm sorry.

1394
01:48:18,889 --> 01:48:20,550
I'll tell tem, sweetheart.

1395
01:48:33,937 --> 01:48:36,167
Remember that story
you were reading to me?

1396
01:48:36,840 --> 01:48:37,932
Yes.

1397
01:48:45,415 --> 01:48:48,441
Do you think that
I could be her tonight?

1398
01:48:50,053 --> 01:48:51,145
Would that be all right?

1399
01:48:52,589 --> 01:48:54,181
You know what we could do?

1400
01:48:54,324 --> 01:48:57,191
Maybe we could get a car
and we could go for a ride.

1401
01:48:58,095 --> 01:49:02,031
We could get out of here,
just go someplace. You want to?

1402
01:49:02,533 --> 01:49:05,093
I don't think so. Not tonight, darling.

1403
01:49:05,235 --> 01:49:06,896
Come on. Why not?

1404
01:49:07,671 --> 01:49:09,036
Wait a minute.

1405
01:49:11,608 --> 01:49:13,542
Why did you call me darling?

1406
01:49:13,677 --> 01:49:15,076
I don't know you.

1407
01:49:15,212 --> 01:49:17,942
What's going on here?
Am I supposed to know you?

1408
01:49:18,081 --> 01:49:20,106
-Allie.
-No. No! No!

1409
01:49:20,250 --> 01:49:21,581
Sweetheart.

1410
01:49:21,718 --> 01:49:24,710
-I love you. Stay with me. Don't leave.
-No!

1411
01:49:25,822 --> 01:49:29,314
-Who are you?
-I'm Noah. I'm Noah and you're Allie.

1412
01:49:29,459 --> 01:49:31,791
What do you want?
What are you doing here?

1413
01:49:31,929 --> 01:49:34,557
-Come on, baby.
-Don't come near me. Don't come near me.

1414
01:49:34,698 --> 01:49:37,929
-Allie, Allie...
-Help! Help!

1415
01:49:38,068 --> 01:49:39,729
-Help me!
-Calm down, Allie. Calm down.

1416
01:49:39,870 --> 01:49:41,667
Calm down. lt's all right, sweetie.

1417
01:49:41,805 --> 01:49:43,102
-lt's all right, baby. Come on.
-Leg me go!

1418
01:49:43,240 --> 01:49:46,368
-Calm down, Allie.
-Leave me alone.

1419
01:49:46,510 --> 01:49:47,704
lt's all right. Doc!

1420
01:49:47,844 --> 01:49:50,836
-Somebody help me!
-Allie, calm down. Doctor!

1421
01:49:50,981 --> 01:49:53,211
-Talk to me.
-Hurry up. She's sundowning.

1422
01:49:53,350 --> 01:49:54,578
Somebody help me!

1423
01:49:54,718 --> 01:49:57,949
-Calm down. Get here arm.
-Okay, two cc's Halop--

1424
01:49:58,088 --> 01:50:00,386
-Calm down, Allie.
-One. Two.

1425
01:50:00,524 --> 01:50:01,650
Three.

1426
01:50:02,826 --> 01:50:03,986
Allie, it's all right.

1427
01:50:04,127 --> 01:50:07,324
-lt's all right.
-You're okay. Let's take a look.

1428
01:50:07,464 --> 01:50:10,297
-Let's take a look. Yeah, she's fine.
-Good.

1429
01:50:10,434 --> 01:50:13,494
-Just breathe. Stay calm.
-Just fine.

1430
01:50:13,637 --> 01:50:16,606
-Breathe in and out through your mouth.
-Relax.

1431
01:50:16,740 --> 01:50:19,368
-You're going to be okay, Allie.
-Relax. lt's all right.

1432
01:50:19,509 --> 01:50:20,737
You're fine now.

1433
01:51:20,137 --> 01:51:21,570
Morning, Mr. Calhoun.

1434
01:51:23,340 --> 01:51:24,739
Mr. Calhoun?

1435
01:51:26,710 --> 01:51:28,473
Call Dr. Fonatant at MUSC, okay?

1436
01:51:28,612 --> 01:51:32,810
I've got no BP, no pulse, nothing.
Let them know we're in full arrest.

1437
01:51:32,949 --> 01:51:34,780
-Call me on my cell!
-Okay, will do.

1438
01:51:53,570 --> 01:51:55,162
We talked about this.

1439
01:51:55,305 --> 01:51:57,364
lt's all right, now. Come on.

1440
01:51:57,507 --> 01:52:00,203
Come on, precious. Come on. Let's go.

1441
01:52:00,343 --> 01:52:04,473
lt's okay, baby.
Come on. You know Mr. Holmes.

1442
01:52:56,433 --> 01:52:58,833
Oh, Mr. Calhoun.

1443
01:52:59,469 --> 01:53:00,663
Welcome back.

1444
01:53:01,171 --> 01:53:04,607
-How do you feel?
-Fine. Fit as a fiddle.

1445
01:53:05,208 --> 01:53:06,698
Where you going?

1446
01:53:06,843 --> 01:53:09,835
I was just taking a walk. I can't sleep.

1447
01:53:10,781 --> 01:53:13,477
You know it's against the rules.

1448
01:53:13,617 --> 01:53:14,606
Yeah, I know.

1449
01:53:16,019 --> 01:53:18,749
You weren't really going for a walk,
were you?

1450
01:53:19,156 --> 01:53:21,147
You were going to see Miss Allie.

1451
01:53:22,726 --> 01:53:26,127
I just got out of the hospital
and I miss her.

1452
01:53:26,997 --> 01:53:28,726
Mr. Calhoun...

1453
01:53:28,865 --> 01:53:32,062
...I'm sorry but I can't let you
see her tonight.

1454
01:53:32,202 --> 01:53:34,830
You'll have to go back to your room.

1455
01:53:37,207 --> 01:53:38,640
As for me...

1456
01:53:38,775 --> 01:53:42,404
...I'm going to go downstairs
and get myself a cup of coffee.

1457
01:53:43,013 --> 01:53:45,675
I won't be back to check
on you for a while.

1458
01:53:46,049 --> 01:53:48,745
So don't do anything foolish.

1459
01:54:44,374 --> 01:54:45,602
Hi.

1460
01:54:55,318 --> 01:54:56,285
Noah.

1461
01:55:02,525 --> 01:55:03,617
Hi, sweetheart.

1462
01:55:05,262 --> 01:55:08,129
I'm sorry I haven't been able
to be here to read to you.

1463
01:55:09,799 --> 01:55:11,699
I didn't know what to do.

1464
01:55:12,402 --> 01:55:14,370
I was afraid you were never coming back.

1465
01:55:14,504 --> 01:55:16,438
Oh, I'll always come back.

1466
01:55:21,945 --> 01:55:24,641
What's going to happen...

1467
01:55:24,948 --> 01:55:28,509
...when I can't remember
anything anymore?

1468
01:55:29,986 --> 01:55:31,544
What will you do?

1469
01:55:31,955 --> 01:55:33,616
I'll be here.

1470
01:55:34,357 --> 01:55:35,654
I'll never leave you.

1471
01:55:45,835 --> 01:55:47,530
I need to ask you something.

1472
01:55:48,405 --> 01:55:49,895
What is it, sweetheart?

1473
01:55:54,678 --> 01:55:56,339
Do you think...

1474
01:55:57,714 --> 01:56:02,242
...that our love can create miracles?

1475
01:56:03,420 --> 01:56:04,648
Yes, I do.

1476
01:56:06,756 --> 01:56:10,123
That's what brings you back
to me each time.

1477
01:56:18,368 --> 01:56:20,165
Do you think our love...

1478
01:56:21,538 --> 01:56:23,972
...could take us away together?

1479
01:56:30,413 --> 01:56:34,008
I think our love can do anything
we want it to.

1480
01:56:47,364 --> 01:56:48,353
I love you.

1481
01:56:50,100 --> 01:56:51,499
I love you, Allie.

1482
01:57:09,119 --> 01:57:10,143
Good night.

1483
01:57:11,588 --> 01:57:12,748
Good night.

1484
01:57:18,495 --> 01:57:20,156
I'll be seeing you.
